1
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:32,980
=The Secret of the Lost Pearl=

2
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:34,940
=Episode 1=
(Fiction. Do not imitate.)

3
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:51,100
(Yelia City)

4
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:00,790
Professor, watch out!

5
00:01:05,340 --> 00:01:09,780
(Professor Chen, archaeologist)

6
00:01:18,230 --> 00:01:19,070
Professor Chen!

7
00:01:19,670 --> 00:01:20,510
Leave!

8
00:01:20,510 --> 00:01:21,680
That area's about to collapse!

9
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:26,460
(Li Ke, team member)

10
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:28,790
Professor Chen, leave now!

11
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:45,950
Hold on.

12
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:57,380
(Chen Youxi, team member)

13
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,840
Chubby, you're too heavy!

14
00:01:59,040 --> 00:01:59,880
Of course.

15
00:02:00,070 --> 00:02:01,430
That's why I'm called Chubby.

16
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:04,000
Hold tight, don't let go!

17
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,840
Chen,

18
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,310
every fight comes with sacrifices.

19
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:10,280
Take care of my mom for me.

20
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,750
Chubby!

21
00:02:31,140 --> 00:02:35,500
(He Shutong, team member)

22
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:37,470
Ms. He.

23
00:02:37,870 --> 00:02:38,910
Ms. He,

24
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,960
I owe you my life again.

25
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:42,680
I'll treat you to a movie.

26
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,080
Watch out!

27
00:03:25,590 --> 00:03:27,080
Professor Chen, are you crazy?

28
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:28,080
That's a trap!

29
00:03:41,910 --> 00:03:42,963
- Chen Youxi!
- Watch out!

30
00:03:50,150 --> 00:03:51,800
That's right; it's the one.

31
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,560
In 30 years,

32
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:55,710
the greatest archaeological finding.

33
00:03:56,253 --> 00:03:57,752
With this as proof, the trade history

34
00:03:57,763 --> 00:03:59,656
between the Central Plains
and the West Regions

35
00:03:59,667 --> 00:04:00,817
can be traced back 500 years.

36
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:02,870
I've seen it with my own eyes.

37
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,710
Now, I can die without regret.

38
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:24,110
Professor!

39
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:36,830
Why didn't you return my calls?

40
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,430
International calls cost a fortune.

41
00:05:39,430 --> 00:05:40,750
It's not something I have to say.

42
00:05:40,870 --> 00:05:41,870
Of course, it is.

43
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:42,816
I'm telling you

44
00:05:42,827 --> 00:05:44,190
about Professor Chen's condition.

45
00:05:44,190 --> 00:05:45,430
He's shown great improvement.

46
00:05:45,630 --> 00:05:46,560
That's great news.

47
00:05:46,870 --> 00:05:48,160
If Professor Chen lost his mind,

48
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:50,270
it'd be a huge loss for archeology.

49
00:05:51,070 --> 00:05:52,000
And you?

50
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,270
Come abroad for a check‑up?

51
00:05:53,280 --> 00:05:54,160
No need.

52
00:05:54,180 --> 00:05:55,600
I only got a scar on me.

53
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,680
No other symptoms at all.

54
00:05:57,070 --> 00:05:58,560
But Chubby told me

55
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,950
your chest hurts pretty often.

56
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,430
That traitor.

57
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:03,950
I'll handle your visa.

58
00:06:03,980 --> 00:06:04,890
I'll buy the tickets.

59
00:06:04,901 --> 00:06:06,059
I'll cover the medical bills.

60
00:06:06,070 --> 00:06:06,910
Deal?

61
00:06:07,190 --> 00:06:08,070
No need.

62
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,190
My life isn't worth spending
that much on.

63
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,390
The doctor told me

64
00:06:11,510 --> 00:06:13,480
that Professor Chen has improved a lot,

65
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:15,310
but since the illness is rare,

66
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,800
there aren't many clinical cases,

67
00:06:17,270 --> 00:06:18,680
so better treatment isn't possible.

68
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:20,130
Your arrival

69
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,270
is good for everyone.

70
00:06:23,630 --> 00:06:25,160
Are you into embroidered shoes?

71
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:26,430
What for?

72
00:06:26,463 --> 00:06:27,750
Don't try to change the subject.

73
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:28,936
I'm not changing the subject.

74
00:06:29,070 --> 00:06:30,600
I just got a burial item yesterday.

75
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:32,360
Didn't you stop collecting those?

76
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:33,680
Someone forced it on me.

77
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:34,600
It feels kind of eerie.

78
00:06:35,070 --> 00:06:35,910
What do you mean?

79
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:37,963
The embroidery and fabric

80
00:06:37,974 --> 00:06:39,120
are both incredibly delicate.

81
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,390
It's pretty well preserved.

82
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,520
But the color is too bright.

83
00:06:42,531 --> 00:06:43,881
Normally, if it came from a tomb,

84
00:06:43,892 --> 00:06:45,196
the moment it's exposed to light,

85
00:06:45,223 --> 00:06:46,560
it should oxidize and fade.

86
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,693
It shouldn't look like this.

87
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,630
That means it's fake.

88
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:51,480
That's unlikely.

89
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,310
This kind of filigree work

90
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:54,870
was lost as early as the Ming dynasty.

91
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,480
You'll understand once you see it.

92
00:06:56,830 --> 00:06:57,670
Then,

93
00:06:57,950 --> 00:06:59,680
bring it over and show me.

94
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:08,760
Hello?

95
00:07:09,510 --> 00:07:10,350
Chen Youxi?

96
00:07:13,430 --> 00:07:14,270
Hello?

97
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:16,270
Hello?

98
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:17,640
Chen Youxi?

99
00:07:40,070 --> 00:07:41,040
Chen!

100
00:07:41,950 --> 00:07:43,600
Chen! Chen!

101
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,510
Chen, hang in there.

102
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:13,510
The capillaries in your chest
keep expanding.

103
00:08:13,950 --> 00:08:15,720
It's already affecting

104
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:17,160
your heart's blood supply.

105
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:19,160
Judging by how fast
this illness is progressing,

106
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:21,390
your time is running short.

107
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:24,240
My personal advice:

108
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,750
Keep a regular routine.

109
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:27,016
Avoid intense physical activity.

110
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:30,360
How long do I have left?

111
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,200
Three months.

112
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:35,000
That's the most optimistic estimate.

113
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:46,200
Kids,

114
00:08:47,390 --> 00:08:48,630
what we're looking at here

115
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:51,390
was a mysterious mask found recently

116
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,550
by archaeologists

117
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:54,750
in the Hetian region.

118
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:56,630
But suddenly,

119
00:08:56,630 --> 00:08:57,790
it vanished without a trace.

120
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:01,630
Without our archaeologists' discovery,

121
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:04,720
historians wouldn't have proved
the existence

122
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,320
of this ancient civilization.

123
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,320
This mask...

124
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:12,870
Alright, kids.

125
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,320
One of the people
who discovered this mask

126
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:17,240
is here with us today.

127
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:18,790
Let's all have him

128
00:09:18,790 --> 00:09:20,320
share with us his experience, okay?

129
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,320
Sure!

130
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:31,480
I passed out the moment I saw it.

131
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,120
I slept for three days.

132
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:35,960
You're the expert here.

133
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,870
Help me figure out what this really is.

134
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,960
I've seen similar patterns.

135
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:42,390
Hold on a sec.

136
00:09:47,150 --> 00:09:48,320
Back in 1968,

137
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:49,870
a foreign research team

138
00:09:49,870 --> 00:09:52,240
salvaged a stone pillar
from underwater in Peru.

139
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:55,000
On those pillars and ruins,

140
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,320
there once appeared
a mysterious eye symbol.

141
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:00,910
It's exactly like the scar on my body.

142
00:10:02,550 --> 00:10:04,120
Does it link

143
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:06,150
to the Nether Ruins?

144
00:10:07,870 --> 00:10:09,630
The Minoan civilization of Greece.

145
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:12,910
The ancient Nabataean civilization.

146
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:15,390
The mysteriously vanished Clovis people.

147
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,240
Their records show

148
00:10:17,360 --> 00:10:19,200
the same eye pattern.

149
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:22,120
This can't be a coincidence.

150
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,000
We also found proof

151
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:26,600
in more ruins.

152
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:27,590
Look.

153
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,160
What did you say?

154
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,360
We've got a new assignment.

155
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:06,790
- Where?
- Yunling.

156
00:11:06,790 --> 00:11:08,240
It's from Curator Zhu's lead.

157
00:11:09,030 --> 00:11:10,480
Tight schedule, urgent mission.

158
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:11,870
Tomorrow morning at seven,

159
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:13,183
meet at the train station.

160
00:11:37,870 --> 00:11:38,710
Take this.

161
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:39,960
Take it easy.

162
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:42,510
No need. It's just right.

163
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:44,120
Alright, take care.

164
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:55,780
(Lu Di, team member)

165
00:11:57,270 --> 00:12:07,480
♪With the strength to move mountains♪

166
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:13,750
♪But fate turns against me♪

167
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:19,910
♪What can I do without my steed♪

168
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:28,790
♪Yu, what should I do with you♪

169
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:51,120
This town doesn't look bad at all.

170
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:52,560
Yeah.

171
00:12:53,970 --> 00:12:54,840
Lu.

172
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:55,953
Have you ever been here?

173
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,390
Why would I come here?

174
00:12:58,390 --> 00:12:59,960
Such a tiny spot.

175
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:03,150
You sound
like you only hang out in big cities.

176
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,240
If it weren't for us...

177
00:13:05,510 --> 00:13:07,390
The goods are here; gather around.

178
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:12,150
Someone's trailing us.

179
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,280
Don't look back.

180
00:13:15,510 --> 00:13:16,910
They're following again.

181
00:13:17,510 --> 00:13:18,360
Let's split up.

182
00:13:19,510 --> 00:13:20,390
Don't split up.

183
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:21,550
What if they attack us

184
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:22,840
when we're alone?

185
00:13:23,336 --> 00:13:24,270
Tonight at Xuanyi Dock.

186
00:13:24,270 --> 00:13:25,120
Catch the last boat.

187
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:25,990
Stay sharp.

188
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,320
Go.

189
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:34,030
Chen Youxi and his crew split up.

190
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,320
Follow them.

191
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:44,550
Chen said to meet at the dock.

192
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:46,600
You wandering around like this
is useless.

193
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:47,440
Do what you want.

194
00:13:53,910 --> 00:13:54,750
Stop right there.

195
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:57,590
Don't run.

196
00:14:00,870 --> 00:14:01,710
Stop!

197
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:03,590
Don't run!

198
00:14:05,150 --> 00:14:05,990
Hurry!

199
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:19,230
Go!

200
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:27,510
Stay still.

201
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,720
I was just thinking what to ask.

202
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:31,688
And you knocked him out.

203
00:14:31,699 --> 00:14:32,769
We didn't get any answers.

204
00:14:33,030 --> 00:14:34,000
If he really answered,

205
00:14:34,033 --> 00:14:35,246
would you even understand him?

206
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:36,390
That's true.

207
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,360
Move!

208
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:38,320
Let's go.

209
00:14:45,270 --> 00:14:46,120
Run then.

210
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,360
Keep running.

211
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,550
Jump

212
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:51,910
if you dare!

213
00:14:51,910 --> 00:14:52,910
- I'm not crazy.
- Jump!

214
00:14:55,650 --> 00:14:56,490
Seriously?

215
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,790
I swear that slick guy

216
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,120
has some dirty trick

217
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,360
planned for us.

218
00:15:33,630 --> 00:15:35,120
Why, Lu? Regretting it?

219
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:37,030
Of course not.

220
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,270
If you regret it, tell us.

221
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:40,960
We wouldn't laugh at you.

222
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,030
Exactly.

223
00:15:42,790 --> 00:15:43,750
Listen to me, guys.

224
00:15:44,030 --> 00:15:45,080
I'm a well-known

225
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,790
artifact appraiser.

226
00:15:46,910 --> 00:15:48,270
I've watched my family

227
00:15:48,270 --> 00:15:49,670
trade antiques and jade.

228
00:15:49,790 --> 00:15:51,480
I've seen my share of treasures.

229
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,360
But when this piece came to us,

230
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:55,270
it was already oxidized.

231
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:56,720
I keep wondering

232
00:15:57,080 --> 00:16:00,440
what it looked like before it aged.

233
00:16:00,630 --> 00:16:02,150
If I could just see that once,

234
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:03,433
I'd die with no regrets.

235
00:16:04,670 --> 00:16:06,790
You've got to have something
to hope for in life.

236
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,720
Back when I explored tombs,

237
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:10,270
I was always scared I'd die there.

238
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:11,670
But fate kept me alive.

239
00:16:11,670 --> 00:16:13,270
Now, every day I wake up,

240
00:16:13,422 --> 00:16:14,738
it feels like I've won something.

241
00:16:14,790 --> 00:16:15,960
When I went to the museum,

242
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:17,670
seeing the guide giving a tour,

243
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:18,590
I thought,

244
00:16:18,910 --> 00:16:21,270
however rich or powerful you are,

245
00:16:21,510 --> 00:16:23,320
without me, you'd see nothing.

246
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:27,480
Chen doesn't chase fame or fortune.

247
00:16:27,870 --> 00:16:29,790
He just hopes to get some praise.

248
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,670
Give it two more years.

249
00:16:31,790 --> 00:16:33,870
Curator Zhu might marry
his daughter to you.

250
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:39,150
What on earth is this?

251
00:17:13,290 --> 00:17:16,390
♪A tiny ark sails;
the sky opens its eyes♪

252
00:17:18,070 --> 00:17:21,750
♪Stillness in motion,
the earth plays its chord♪

253
00:17:22,810 --> 00:17:27,390
♪A leaf falls;
we cross through time and space♪

254
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:34,540
♪In a blink, all things rest
upon our hands♪

255
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:46,120
♪La la♪

256
00:17:52,870 --> 00:17:54,860
♪No line divides the border♪

257
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:57,640
♪Nothing limits your performance♪

258
00:17:57,640 --> 00:18:00,010
♪Everything shows perfect harmony♪

259
00:18:00,010 --> 00:18:02,700
♪Love circles the sky,
the earth, and our faith♪

260
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,910
♪Hey hey hey♪

261
00:18:07,240 --> 00:18:09,060
♪Hey hey hey♪

262
00:18:11,710 --> 00:18:12,710
♪Hey hey♪

263
00:18:12,860 --> 00:18:13,860
♪Hey hey♪

264
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:16,400
♪Hey hey♪

265
00:18:18,030 --> 00:18:22,230
♪Step into the galaxy of colors♪

266
00:18:22,820 --> 00:18:26,530
♪Stars connect our hearts as one♪

267
00:18:28,810 --> 00:18:31,030
♪No difference between you and me♪

268
00:18:31,310 --> 00:18:33,640
♪No lead or side role on this stage♪

269
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:35,850
♪A perfect life is something we share♪

270
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:38,350
♪Love declares across the sky and earth♪

271
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:44,070
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

272
00:18:44,070 --> 00:18:48,920
♪Time and space go beyond all bounds♪

273
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:53,770
♪Huo la yi ya, huo la yi ya♪

274
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:55,860
♪This is our world♪

275
00:18:55,860 --> 00:19:00,890
♪Shining lives bring the change♪

276
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:07,980
♪In a blink, to forever♪
